# Version bump after CSS/JS changes (required)

**When you edit any CSS or JS in this project, you MUST update the cache-busting version in `site/index.html` and keep CSS and JS in sync.**

In `site/index.html`, update **every** `?v=...` to the **same** new value (e.g. `2.0.1` → `2.0.2`):

- Preload for `styles.min.css`
- Stylesheet `href` for `styles.min.css`
- Script `src` for `script.min.js`

Use one version for both assets. Whether you changed only CSS or only JS, bump all three to the same new value so they stay in sync. Increment each time (e.g. patch: `2.0.2` → `2.0.3`).

Minification is handled by the backend (CI/deploy); do not run `npm run build` in this workflow.
